## Context

companion-paper.qmd has good lit review and data sections but uses old
methods (KMeans clusters, JS on proportions, cosine on centroids). The
ChatGPT note (docs/ChatGPT-20260415-MethodForAutoPeriodization-v1.md)
provides a clean methods framework. Inject as scaffolding, rewrite in
project voice.

## Actions

1. Insert ChatGPT note §1-12 as HTML comments in companion-paper.qmd,
   section by section, as scaffolding for the rewrite.

2. Rewrite methods section (§4) following the plan:
   - §4.1: Objective and epistemic stance
   - §4.2: Representations (embedding PCA-32, TF-IDF, co-citation graph)
   - §4.3: Temporal segmentation (sliding windows, w=3)
   - §4.4: Distributional comparison (Energy, JS, Louvain+JS)
   - §4.5: Statistical inference (permutation Z-scores, Z > 2 threshold)
   - §4.6: Transition zone detection + multi-signal validation
   - §4.7: Censored-gap confirmation (two-pass)
   - §4.8: Robustness (equal-n subsampling, sensitivity, PELT)
   - §4.9: Interpretation (terms, documents, communities)

3. Delete old §4 (KMeans clusters) and old §5 (censored-gap, seed-axis).

4. Write results section (§5) using corrected pipeline outputs:
   - Z-score time series for 6 methods
   - Transition zones with multi-signal validation
   - Censored-gap confirmation results
   - Interpretation at each validated zone
   - Reference Oeconomia manuscript for historical interpretation

5. Update abstract, introduction, discussion.

6. Run `/review-pr-prose` — AI-tells auditor must pass on rewritten sections.

## Writing rules

- Ghost mode: Economist style, no AI tells
- Show, don't tell: specific dates, documents, actors
- Epistemic honesty: report what the data shows, not what we hoped

## Test

```python
def test_companion_paper_sections():
    """Companion paper has all required sections."""
    text = Path("content/companion-paper.qmd").read_text()
    for section in ["Objective", "Representations", "Temporal segmentation",
                    "Distributional comparison", "Statistical inference",
                    "Transition zone", "Censored-gap", "Interpretation"]:
        assert section.lower() in text.lower()
```

## Exit criteria

- All 9 method subsections written in project voice
- Results section uses corrected pipeline outputs
- `/review-pr-prose` passes (no AI tells)
- `quarto render content/companion-paper.qmd` succeeds
